msgid "## Complete Lattices\n"
"\n"
"A normal lattice has supremums for any 2 elements. A **Complete Lattice** has supremums and infimums for *every* subset, even infinite ones! (Think of the power set of a type).\n"
"\n"
"Because the empty set ¬ß0 also has a supremum, every complete lattice is guaranteed to have a least element, called ¬ß1 (bot), and a greatest element, called ¬ß2 (top). Let's look at ¬ß3."
