#: Game.Levels.PosetWorld.Level01
msgid "## Partial Order Definition\n"
"\n"
"A *partial order* (or a partially ordered type) is a type ¬ß0 equipped with a concept of ¬ß1 satisfying three fundamental axioms:\n"
"1. **Reflexivity:** ¬ß2\n"
"2. **Antisymmetry:** ¬ß3\n"
"3. **Transitivity:** ¬ß4\n"
"\n"
"Examples of partial orders include the natural numbers, the real numbers, and the type ¬ß5 of subsets of a type ¬ß6 (where ¬ß7 means ¬ß8).\n"
"\n"
"Also, note that there is some strange ¬ß9 text in your objects. This simply means that your objects\n"
"are instances of certain classes, for example that X is a partial order.\n"
"\n"
"## Goal for this level\n"
"\n"
